 HN59[
] Section 3 of the Sherman Act provides in pertinent part: "Every contract, combination * * * or conspiracy, in restraint of trade or commerce in any Territory of the United States * * * or 
between any such Territory * * * and * * * States * * * is declared illegal."

 It is clear HN4[
] under Section 412 of the Act (49 U.S.C. § 1382) that the Board can only approve and thereby immunize 
agreements to which "air carriers" are parties.  Additionally, HN5[
] under Section 411 (49 U.S.C. § 1381), the Board can issue 
cease and desist orders against air carriers, foreign air carriers, and ticket agents which are engaged in unfair methods of 
competition.

 See also Fisons Ltd. v. United States, 458 F.2d 1241 (CA7), cert. denied, 405 U.S. 1041 (1972) (service of process); 
Farbenfabriken Bayer, A. G. v. United States, 1968 CCH Trade Cas. para. 72,570 (CADC), cert. denied, 393 U.S. 959 (1968) 
(quasi in rem jurisdiction).

 In view of our disposition of this case, we find no occasion to express any view concerning possible pre-emption by the 
N.L.R.B. See generally San Diego Buliding Trades Council v. Garmon, 359 U.S. 236, 3 L. Ed. 2d 775, 79 S. Ct. 773 (1959); 
Motor Coach Employees v. Lockridge, 403 U.S. 274, 91 S. Ct. 1909, 29 L. Ed. 2d 473 (1971).

